casebody.data:
Travis Lee KINDER, Respondent,
v.
KANSAS CITY AUTO ACQUISITIONS, INC., Appellant. WD 80999 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: April 24, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied May 29, 2018
Rehearing Denied May 29, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied August 21, 2018 Mark W. Schmitz, Kansas City, MO, for respondent. Gary J. Willnauer, Kansas City, MO, for appellant. Before Division Three: Victor C. Howard, Presiding Judge, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge and Gary D. Witt, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

Appellants Kansas City Auto Acquisitions Inc., d/b/a State Line Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram, and David Wayne Caldwell ("Caldwell") (collectively, "State Line") appeal the order of the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri denying State Line's Motion to Stay Proceedings and Compel Arbitration ("Motion") in a civil action brought against it by Travis Kinder and Nicole Kinder (collectively, the "Kinders"). The order is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
